#PixelBuds Pro 2 are a huge leap forward in our relentless pursuit of combining the ultimate fit and comfort with great sound and helpfulness.

👂 A fluid and organic form, sculpted specifically for the unique geometry of the ear using 45 million data points
🪶 27% smaller and 24% lighter than the first generation Pixel Buds Pro while offering premium sound quality and 2x more powerful noise cancellation¹
👌 Twist-to-adjust stabilizer locks them securely in place during workouts or easily adjusts the other way for all-day wear
🙌 Includes four eartip sizes (XS, S, M, L) to make it possible for almost everyone to achieve a great seal and incredible comfort
🎨 Choose from four colors: understated neutrals like Porcelain and Hazel or the new bold and expressive Peony and Wintergreen
🔋 Protected by a delightful case with a built-in speaker to help you find your device more easily² and powers up to 30 hours with Active Noise Cancellation³
♻️ Comes in 100% plastic-free packaging that's lighter and easier to recycle⁴

Find your perfect fit at GoogleStore.com

¹Compared to Pixel Buds Pro (1st gen). Based on mid-frequency ranges (400Hz-2kHz).
²Requires earbuds and case to be nearby and connected to compatible device. Requires buds to be connected with Fast Pair to a device running Android 9 or newer, with location history enabled.
³All listening times are approximate and were measured using music playback with pre-production hardware and software, with fully charged Pixel Buds Pro 2 and case, and other features disabled. Case is used to recharge Pixel Buds Pro 2. Charging times are approximate. Use of other features will decrease battery life. Battery life depends on device, features enabled, usage, environment and many other factors. Actual battery life may be lower.
⁴Based on retail packaging (excluding adhesive materials and required plastic stickers) as shipped by Google for products launched in August 2024 and onward. To meet the request of some retail partners, stickers and/or security tags are applied to some packaging variations and may contain plastic.

#Pixel9 is made to hold on to 🤲

✨ Redesigned with Corning® Gorilla® Glass Victus® 2 front and back glass, curved edges, and a smooth, durable frame¹
💎 Crafted with premium materials, the glossy glass back complemented by beautiful matte finish metals offers tactility with a subtle reflective sheen
🔆 The 6.3-inch Actua display is brighter than ever, with thinner borders for an immersive viewing experience²
📷 Evolved camera bar that's sleeker and more sculpted with strikingly simple geometry, in a nod to high end photography
💧 Built for longevity and can handle everyday drops, spills, and dust¹
🎨 New bold and expressive colors Peony and Wintergreen join the lineup alongside elegant Obsidian and Porcelain
♻️ Made with recycled materials,³ including the 100% recycled aluminum frame,⁴ and comes in 100% plastic-free packaging⁵

¹Designed to comply with dust and water protection rating IP68 under IEC standard 60529 when each device leaves the factory but the device is not water or dust proof. The accessories are not water or dust resistant. Water resistance and dust resistance are not permanent conditions and will diminish or be lost over time due to normal wear and tear, device repair, disassembly or damage. Phone is not drop/tumble proof and dropping your device may result in loss of water/dust resistance. Damage from drops, tumbles, and other external forces are not covered under warranty. Liquid damage voids the warranty. See g.co/pixel/water for details.
²Screen has rounded corners. When measured diagonally as a rectangle, screen is 6.3 inches. Actual viewable area is less. Dimension may vary by configuration and manufacturing process.
³These recycled materials are at least 18% of product based on weight.
⁴These recycled materials are at least 12% of product based on weight.
⁵Based on retail packaging (excluding adhesive materials and required plastic stickers) as shipped by Google. To meet the request of some retail partners, stickers and/or security tags are applied to some packaging variations and may contain plastic.

YouTube ❤️ Los Angeles

YouTube and @google are contributing $15 million to organizations providing immediate relief in LA in support of our creator community, including Emergency Network Los Angeles, @americanredcross, @funds4disaster and the Institute for Nonprofit News, together with Google.org.

Los Angeles is the heart of entertainment and storytelling, and where many YouTube creators, artists, partners and our employees call home. We’re heartbroken by the devastation from the wildfires and want to support the city as it rebuilds.

We’ll continue to support recovery and rebuilding efforts alongside our partners across the industry. In moments like these, we see the power of communities coming together to support each other. The strength and resilience of the YouTube community is like no other.
